Dear students,

Please note that you are required to attend your Workshops first before the Applied Classes. 

If you need further assistance, please complete the Timetabling Help Form.

Kind regards,

Scheduling Operations

PASS-Optional-JTU.message:
Peer Assisted Study Sessions (PASS) is an optional, unit-based study support program. Each session is 1-hour and you?ll join your classmates and a friendly peer who is your PASS leader. The PASS leader will help you understand the unit content and share their study tips with you.

You can join PASS at any time in the semester. Our tip is to join as many sessions as you can and ask your questions so you feel more confident with your studies!

PASS assists with: - What to learn (unit content)
- How to learn (study skills)
- Keeping motivated
- Making friends with classmates

PASS commences in Week 2 (week commencing 31 July).

PASS session registration on Allocate+ opens 10am, Monday 24 July.

You don?t need to be registered in Allocate+ to attend sessions. Please visit the PASS Sem 2 Moodle and click on this unit?s tile. There you?ll find session times and Zoom information/venue details. Please add the session information to your personal calendar so you get weekly attendance reminders.

There are limited seats in the on-campus sessions, so make sure you attend if registered.

We?re here to help! Reach us at pass.registration@monash.edu.
